  "articleBody": "<!-- Page 12 --><article>\n\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">the angels of the seventh seal - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verses 1 to 2</h5>\n\n        <header>\n          <p class=\"no-puce\">chapter 8</p>\n        </header>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-1\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-1\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"01\">When he opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.</li>\n            <li value=\"02\">I saw the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">seven angels</span> who stand before God, and <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">seven trumpets</span> were given to them.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/7-anges-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-8-1\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the angels of the seventh seal”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the angels of the seventh seal”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"608\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/7-anges-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the angels of the seventh seal”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-8-1\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">who stand before God, and seven trumpets were given to them</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verse 2.</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">the angel of the altar - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verses 3</h5>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-3\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-3\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"03\">Another angel came and stood over the altar, having a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">golden censer</span>. Much incense was given to him, that he should add it to the prayers of all the saints on the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">golden altar</span> which was before the throne.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/autel-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-8-3\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the angel of the altar”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the angel of the altar”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"902\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/autel-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the angel of the altar”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-8-3\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">having a golden censer</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verse 3.</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-4\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-4\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"04\">The smoke of the incense, with the prayers of the saints, went up before God out of the angel's hand.</li>\n            <li value=\"05\">The angel took the censer, and he filled it with the fire of the altar, and threw it on the earth. There followed thunders, sounds, lightnings, and an earthquake.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">fall of the great burning mountain - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verses 6 to 9</h5>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-6\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-6\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"06\">The seven angels who had the seven trumpets prepared themselves to sound.</li>\n            <li value=\"07\">The first sounded, and there followed hail and fire, mixed with blood, and they were thrown to the earth.One third of the earth was burnt up, and one third of the trees were burnt up, and all green grass was burnt up.</li>\n            <li value=\"08\">The second angel sounded, and something like a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">great burning mountain</span> was thrown into the sea. One third of the sea became blood,</li>\n            <li value=\"09\">and one third of the living creatures which were in the sea died. <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">One third of the ships were destroyed</span>.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/bateaux-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-8-4\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, fall of “a great burning mountain was thrown into the sea”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, fall of “a great burning mountain was thrown into the sea”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"502\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/bateaux-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, fall of <a great burning mountain was thrown into the sea”.<br>q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-8-6\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">One third of the ships were destroyed</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verse 8.</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">the fall of the \"wormwood\" star - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verses 10 to 12</h5>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-10\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-10\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"10\">The third angel sounded, and a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">great star fell from the sky, burning like a torch</span>, and it fell on one third of the rivers, and on the springs of the waters.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/absinthe-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-8-10\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the fall of the star called «Wormwood»”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the fall of the star called «Wormwood»”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-diane-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"1268\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/absinthe-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the fall of the star called «Wormwood»”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-8-11\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">a great star fell from the sky, burning like a torch</q> (…) «One third of the waters became wormwood. Many people died from the waters, because they were made bitter», <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verses 8 to 12.</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-11\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-11\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"11\">The name of the star is called «<span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">wormwood</span>». One third of the waters became wormwood. Many people died from the waters, because they were made bitter.</li>\n            <li value=\"12\">The fourth angel sounded, and one third of the sun was struck, and one third of the moon, and one third of the stars; so that one third of them would be darkened, and the day wouldn't shine for one third of it, and the night in the same way.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">the flight of the eagle - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verse 13</h5>\n\n        <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-8-13\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-8-13\">\n          <ol class=\"doc\">\n            <li value=\"13\">\n              <p>I saw, and I heard an <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">eagle</span>, flying in mid heaven, saying with a loud voice,</p>\n              <p class=\"conversation\">\n                “Woe! Woe! Woe for those who dwell on the earth, because of the other voices of the trumpets of the three angels, who are yet to sound!”.\n              </p>\n            </li>\n          </ol>\n        </blockquote>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/aigle-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-8-13\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the flight of the eagle”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the flight of the eagle”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"375\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/aigle-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the flight of the eagle”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-8-13\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">in mid heaven</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 8 verse 13.</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n    \n</article>"
}